image.altText: Usman Khawaja is on his back foot as he punches the ball into the off side as Jonny Bairstow watches on

items.synopsis: Usman Khawaja carries his bat to tea through a positive session for Australia, who remain well behind England's first-innings total on day two of the first Ashes Test. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: Khawaja leads fightback for Australia on day two at Edgbaston

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Big session for Australia, thanks to Usman Khawaja and Travis Head. Cameron Green, too, was showing some intent late. Strangely, in the final over before the break. The English bowlers are struggling to elicit much action right now, and Khawaja and Green are both looking pretty solid out there. But so too was Travis Head. All it takes is one moment to change the game completely.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEA: Australia 4-188 (Khawaja 84, Green 21)

props.alt: Cameron Green completes a cricket shot.

children.content: Big session for Australia, thanks to Usman Khawaja and Travis Head.
Cameron Green, too, was showing some intent late. Strangely, in the final over before the break.
The English bowlers are struggling to elicit much action right now, and Khawaja and Green are both looking pretty solid out there.
But so too was Travis Head. All it takes is one moment to change the game completely.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Travis Head goes for 50! Keeping Moeen on was a great idea it seems for England! Head tried to go down the pitch and, instead of hitting Moeen straight as he has had so much success doing, he tried to work him to midwicket and offered up a relatively simple catch to Zak Crawley at midwicket! Big breakthrough for England just as Australia were getting on top.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! Head gifts a catch to Crawley!

children.content: Travis Head goes for 50! Keeping Moeen on was a great idea it seems for England!

Head tried to go down the pitch and, instead of hitting Moeen straight as he has had so much success doing, he tried to work him to midwicket and offered up a relatively simple catch to Zak Crawley at midwicket!
Big breakthrough for England just as Australia were getting on top.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England's session in a big way, with David Warner, Marnus Labuschagne and Steve Smith back in the sheds after big moments at either end of the session. Usman Khawaja and Travis Head are a dangerous pair, but three wickets in the session is tough sledding for Australia. When England lost three wickets in a session, it wasn't such a big deal because they had more runs on the board. Still, if this pair get their eye in, they have all the time in the world to build a big first-innings total.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: Australia 3-78 (Khawaja 40, Head 8)

props.alt: England players rush to celebrate with Ben Stokes.

children.content: England's session in a big way, with David Warner, Marnus Labuschagne and Steve Smith back in the sheds after big moments at either end of the session.

Usman Khawaja and Travis Head are a dangerous pair, but three wickets in the session is tough sledding for Australia. When England lost three wickets in a session, it wasn't such a big deal because they had more runs on the board.
Still, if this pair get their eye in, they have all the time in the world to build a big first-innings total.
